MemberSignature.Value: public static MonoTouch.CoreGraphics.CGColorSpace CreateIndexed (MonoTouch.CoreGraphics.CGColorSpace baseSpace, int lastIndex, byte[] colorTable);
.method public static hidebysig class MonoTouch.CoreGraphics.CGColorSpace CreateIndexed(class MonoTouch.CoreGraphics.CGColorSpace baseSpace, int32 lastIndex, unsigned int8[] colorTable) cil managed

Docs.param: The colorspace upon which the indexed color space is based
The maximum number of elements in the indexed colorspace (up to 255)
The color table, one byte is allocated for each color component.
Docs.summary: Creates an indexed color space based on the specified colorspace.

remarks.para: An indexed color space allows developers to reprensent colors with a byte value, the actual color rendered is computed by looking up the value in the colortable array.
For example, in an 24-bit RGB colorspace, the color index 2 would be looked up as 3-byte values at index 6, 7 and 8 in the colorTable byte array.
The number of elements in this array is the value of lastIndex multiplied by the number of components in the baseSpace.
